(100, 1, '2018-07-03 12:04:18', '2018-07-03 09:04:18', '[rev_slider alias="slider1"]\r\n\r\nOn January 1, 2016, the transport system of the city consists of 953 streets, total length of roads is 1038,4 km, including asphalt-concrete cover is 779,5 km (75%) and 258,9 km of roads (25%) is without hard cover.\r\n\r\nThe city has nine companies providing public transport services for the population (including one municipal and eight private), serving 85 trails. The vehicle fleets consist of 1025 buses, and 829 of them are used daily. The volume of public transport is 850 thousand passengers per day. Moreover, 14 specialized taxi companies with a total number of vehicle stock as 560 units operate there. The length of the city route network is 3811 km.\r\n\r\nDue to the implementation of the project "Bus Lane", the average speed of buses for 11 of the project streets has increased by 12-15%, the movement interval was reduced to 5-8 minutes. Adaptive control of the project "Intelligent transportation system" covers 42 junctions. Throughput increased by 23%.\r\n\r\nThe city has an international airport "Nursultan Nazarbayev», capable to accept all types of aircraft. A new railway station is built in the South-Eastern part of the city called "Nurly Zhol" near constructing Alleys of the Millennium.\r\n\r\nAt the same time, a terminal for freight wagons will be built in the industrial part of the city near TPP-3.\r\n\r\nSince 2008, the city organized the shipping industry. Akimat of the city within the framework of realization of "Sudohodnyi Esil» program has created specialized enterprise "Esil-Astana". The first navigation opened in 2008.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Transport', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'test-5-en', '', '', '2018-07-03 15:42:09', '2018-07-03 12:42:09', '', 0, 'http://localhost/desc/?p=100', 0, 'post', '', 0),
