(110, 1, '2018-07-03 12:06:59', '2018-07-03 09:06:59', '[rev_slider alias="slider1"]\r\n\r\nThe territory of Astana is 710,2 sq. m. It has a population of over 1 million people; it is 4 times more than in 1998. According to forecasts, 2.5 million people will live in the main city of Kazakhstan by 2050.\r\n\r\nThe status of capital has opened huge prospects of growth and development for Astana. Over the past years, there has been identifiable change not only in the appearance of the city, but also in production, construction, culture, social welfare. Social-economic indicators characterizing the development of the city, demonstrate the current trend of dynamic growth of the real sector of the economy, inflow of investments in market segments and social development of the city. Transferring the capital to Astana, led to the rapid population growth of the city mostly through migration inflow, mainly of highly qualified specialists aged from 20 to 45 years. According to estimates of city officials, the average wage here is equal to the level of wage in petroleum regions of the country, and the unemployment rate is one of the lowest in Kazakhstan. A positive factor in population increase in Astana is also increasing levels of fertility and marriage.', 'The Population of Astana', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'test-7-en', '', '', '2018-07-03 15:31:46', '2018-07-03 12:31:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost/desc/?p=110', 0, 'post', '', 0),
