(179, 1, '2018-07-03 16:27:20', '2018-07-03 13:27:20', '[rev_slider alias="slider1"]\r\n\r\nPavilion "Nur Alem". There is an interactive way to get acquainted with the traditions and customs of the Kazakh people, to plunge into the nature of Kazakhstan, to play on traditional musical instruments and, of course, to find out about the latest developments in our country. The pavilion is large, beautiful and spacious, filled with homey details and original chips. For example, anyone can take a picture, and then his picture will be in the interactive part, located in the area, which presents a new Kazakhstan development.\r\n\r\nPavilions our neighbors — the CIS countries. The Russian pavilion talks about the problems of global warming. It also rises the problem of the disappearance of tigers and you can buy national Souvenirs and products. The Uzbek Pavilion — a demonstration of human life in 20-30 years. A key figure of the pavilion — acting car with solar panels. The car is fully functioning on the installed solar panels that feed a battery and a motor vehicle. A special shed — solar-charging station, which powers car battery, is installed along with the car. It is expected that such cars will appear everywhere on the market in 2030. Nowadays cars are still being tested.\r\n\r\nPavilions of European countries — the UK, Spain, Italy, Germany, Serbia, Finland, Switzerland.\r\n\r\nIn the center of the mysterious pavilion of Great Britain, there is a kind of Yurt, rods that light up, feeling the warmth and pressure of a person. In addition, the UK has introduced bulbs made of graphene, which do not heat up when used.\r\n\r\nThe Spanish pavilion was noted for video content and has attracted all lovers of photography. When you enter, the pavilion broadcasts the video of "energy": of earth, water, air, sun, space. In the Italian pavilion, they spoke about the energy crisis in the country and ways of its resolution. In addition to this, the pavilion presents some interesting "schtick" and the portraits of Leonardo da Vinci and Mona Lisa.\r\n\r\nOne of the most "intelligent" of the pavilions can rightly be called the German pavilion — each visitor gets a Smart-ticket at the entrance — small "ticket" that can be attributed to the panel near each exhibit and you can learn about its appointment.\r\n\r\nLeaders in the development of new technologies — Japan, South Korea and China also presented their creations at the exhibition in Astana. These pavilions have received a great popularity among the visitors of the exhibition from the first day.\r\n\r\nThe theme of the Japanese pavilion was the "Smart Mix with Technology", telling about how the Japanese are dealing with the energy problems by using their high technology. The South Korean pavilion theme is "future energy and Smart life". The Pavilion also has a car on hydrogen engine.\r\n\r\nPavilions of the countries of the Arab world, Pakistan, Thailand, Malaysia, and Turkey also surprised visitors with its picturesque.\r\n\r\nParticipants\r\n\r\n100 States and 10 international organizations took part in the EXPO-2017.', 'Pavilions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'pavilions', '', '', '2018-07-03 21:21:43', '2018-07-03 18:21:43', '', 0, 'http://localhost/desc/?p=179', 0, 'post', '', 0),
